title: Union basketball player signs with IU East
text:
Union basketball player signs with IU East The Star Press 11:17 p.m. EDT October 7, 2015 Rylee Davis CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
GIRLS BASKETBALL 
Rylee Davis of Union High School in Modoc, Indiana, is the first member of the 2016 recruiting class to sign her letter of intent to play basketball at Indiana University East. Davis averaged 12.4 points, 8.7 rebounds, 3.3 assists and 2.2 blocks per game her junior year to help Union to a 22-4 record and a sectional championship. She also made the Indiana Basketball Coaches Association Underclass Honorable Mention All-State team as a junior. She is an all-county and all-conference honoree.
